divs: sighting detailsi saw a long shinny cylinder in the north\west sky around 6:54am. as i was going to my car to go to work. the sun was out, and there were no stars in the sky that i could see. i went back into my house and got my camera, this took about 3 minutes; and to my surprise the object was still there. after snapping the first shot, it was gone. i watch the skies every time i go outside, and i've seen a lot of strange crafts in the skies, but this was the first time i was able to get a photo of what i've seen.
